    • collect

      private static <T extends AnnotatedElement> void collect​(T[] potentialTokens, Function<T,​Integer> getModifiers, Function<T,​String> getName, TokenCollector.MyFunction<T,​String> getValue) throws InvocationTargetException
      Collects name-value pairs from an array of potential Tokens. The value must be accessible so the modifiers must include public and static.
      Type Parameters:
      T - an AnnotatedElement, such as a Field or a Method
      Parameters:
      potentialTokens - the array of potential Tokens
      getModifiers - a function to get the modifiers of a T object
      getName - a function to get the name of a T object
      getValue - a function to get the value of a T object
      Throws:
      InvocationTargetException - when there is an uncaught exception in in user code
